A vintage 1990s home office scene with warm amber lighting, featuring an old beige IBM PC AT computer on a wooden desk surrounded by scattered floppy disks, thick spiral-bound software manuals, and a cold cup of coffee. A desk lamp casts a focused cone of light onto the keyboard where hands hover mid-type. Through a window, the deep blue of late night is visible. The room has wood-paneled walls, a small potted plant, and stacked boxes of software. The atmosphere is intimate and nostalgic, capturing the essence of late-night self-taught programming sessions and the dawn of personal computing exploration. Film grain texture, muted earth tones with pops of the classic IBM blue, shot as if through a 35mm camera from the early 1990s.
